1:22 i had one of the most retarded self kiosk encounters ever in Bangkok last year at a McDonald's place
in the US, I choose the thing I want to order then pay at the kiosk and wait for them to call my number to go get my food. at the BKK McDonald's location, I have to choose from the kiosk then printed out the order in a receipt then hand to the cashier to be entered manually into their system then pay at the cashier and wait for the foods ğŸ˜ŒğŸ¤¬
one evening, I return from an afternoon trip from the northern province so I was quite hungry and two Indian families hoarded the kiosks and making long decision on what to eat (waited 5 minutes) so I walked up to the cashier and told them the meal I wanted to order and the lady cashier just pointing her finger at the kiosk. she and her male coworker saw how long they took so I got angry and walk out saying in Thai "I'm angry and don't want to eat anymore (à¸­à¸²à¸£à¸¡à¸“à¹Œà¹€à¸ªà¸µà¸¢à¹à¸¥à¹‰à¸§à¹„à¸¡à¹ˆà¸­à¸¢à¸²à¸ à¸à¸´à¸™à¹à¸¥à¹‰à¸§)" but my brother decided to stay and after another 3 minutes, the male coworker handed the menu to my brother. my brother said that after receiving his order, the Indian families still using the kiosk, there are only two kiosks in that McDonald's. ğŸ™„
